{"title_page": "Essel Group", "text_new": "{{pp-30-500|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Essel Group\n| logo = EsselGroup SVG Logo.svg\n| type = [[Private Company|Private]]\n| foundation = {{start date and age|1926}}\n| founder = [[Jagannath Goenka]]\n| location = [[Mumbai]], [[India]]\n| area_served = [[World]]wide\n| key_people = [[Subhash Chandra]] ([[Chairman]])\n| industry = [[Conglomerate (company)|Conglomerate]]\n| products = [[Mass media|Media]], [[entertainment]], packaging, [[infrastructure]], education, precious metals and technology\n| divisions = [[#Business divisions|See below]]\n| revenue = [[United States dollar|US$]]2.4 billion (2017)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zeelearn.com/about-essel-group/|title=About Essel Group &#124; Zee Learn}}</ref>\n| num_employees = 10,000 (2011)\n| homepage = {{URL|http://www.esselgroup.com/}}\n| Broadcast Area = \n}}\n\n'''Essel Group''' is an Indian [[Conglomerate (company)|conglomerate]] [[holding company]] headquartered in based in [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esselgroup.com/contactus.htm |title=Essel Group |publisher=Essel Group |date= |accessdate=2010-07-16}}</ref> Founded in 1926, the current chairman of the group is [[Subhash Chandra]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report_subhash-chandra-buys-stake-in-uni_1051782 |title=Subhash Chandra buys stake in UNI |publisher=dnaindia.com |date=2006-09-08 |accessdate=2010-07-16}}</ref>\n\n== Business divisions ==\nThe companies under the group are:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rediff.com/money/2007/may/22inter1.htm |title=Subhash Chandra on Zee, DNA & Essel |publisher=Rediff.com |date= |accessdate=2010-07-16}}</ref>\n\n=== Zee Entertainment Enterprises Limited (ZEEL) ===\nThe company was launched in 15 December 1991 as Zee Telefirms Ltd as the Essel group's venture into m[[Mass media|ass media]] and [[entertainment]]  The company launched its first television channel ([[Zee TV]]) on 1 October 1992. The channel is currently the flagship channel of the company which owns a variety of channels under the brand name of Zee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/magazine/profile/story/19940815-subhash-chandra-makes-television-history-with-zee-tv-began-life-running-a-flour-mill-809511-1994-08-15|title=Subhash Chandra makes television history with Zee TV began life running a flour-mill|last=Agarwal|first=Amit|last2=|first2=|date=12 July 2013|website=India Today|language=en|publication-date=15 August 1994|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 February 2020|last3=|first3=|last4=|first4=}}</ref>\n\nThe company was registered on the [[List of BSE Sensex companies|BSE Sensex]] from 2000\u20132005. In 2006, the company was split with the Zee Telefirms Ltd, [[Zee News Ltd]] and [[Wire & Wireless India Ltd]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/zee-telefilms-demerges-into-3-firms-106121401118_1.html|title=Zee Telefilms demerges into 3 firms|date=2006-12-14|work=[[Business Standard]]|access-date=2020-02-28|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe company acquired a majority stake (51%) in ETC Networks. In 2006, they acquired Integrated Subscriber Management Services Limited, and in November 2006, it acquired an 50% stake in Taj television, owner of [[TEN Sports]]. On that same year, the company was rebranded as Zee Entertainment Enterprises. In 2006, the brand name was changed to Zee Entertainment Enterprises Ltd.\n\nIn 2008, Zee Networks launched [[Zee Motion Pictures]] and [[Zee Limelight]] (now [[Zee Studios]]) for the development, production, distribution and marketing of mainstream films in Indian languages, including [[Hindi language|Hindi]], [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Telugu language|Telugu]], [[Kannada language|Kannada]], [[Malayalam language|Malayalam]], [[Bengali language|Bengali]] and [[Marathi language|Marathi]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://businessofcinema.com/bollywood-news/zee-group-launches-two-motion-picture-production-banners/22232|title=Zee Group launches two motion picture production banners|date=2008|publisher=Business of Cinema}}</ref> Some of [[Zee Studios]]'s productions include [[Gadar: Ek Prem Katha]], [[Natsamrat]], [[Sairat]] and [[Rustom (film)|Rustom]].\n\nIn February 2010, the business acquired an additional stake (95%) in TEN Sports.\n\nIn May 2011, Star Den entered into a 50/50 joint venture with [[Zee Turner]] and Zee Entertainment Enterprises (ZEEL) to distribute and market all channels owned by the company and ZEEL, their respective affiliated channels and other third-party channels in India, Nepal and Bhutan.\n\nIn 2015 Zee acquired [[Sarthak TV]], an Odia-language pay-television channel.<ref>[http://www.exchange4media.com/TV/Zee-Entertainment-acquires-Sarthak-Entertainment_60810.html Zee Entertainment Acquires Sarthak Entertainment]</ref> One year later, on 28 July 2016, it launched [[Zee One]], aimed at the German market. A Polish version of the channel was launched in 2017.\n\nIn 2016, Zee launched [[Zee Mundo]], a Spanish-language Bollywood movie channel targeting Latin America.\n\nIn 2017, the company acquired the majority stake of the Reliance Broadcast Network.<ref>{{cite web|author=Bindu D Menon |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/zee-group-buys-into-anil-ambanis-tv-and-radio-businesses/article9378020.ece |title=Zee buys Anil Ambani\u2019s TV, radio biz for \u20b91,900 cr &#124; Business Line |publisher=Thehindubusinessline.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-23}}</ref> It also fully purchased [[9X Media]] and INX Music.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/business/zee-entertainment-fully-acquires-9x-media-and-inx-music-in-a-rs-160-crore-cash-deal-4117103.html |title=Zee Entertainment fully acquires 9X Media and INX Music in Rs 160-crore cash deal |publisher=Firstpost.com |date= |accessdate=2017-11-23}}</ref>\nA partially-owned subsidiary, Diligent Media Corporation, is a publisher of Indian daily newspapers and websites. DMC is a [[joint venture]] between Zee and the [[Dainik Bhaskar]] Group.<ref>{{cite web|title=Indian Newspapers and News Sites|url=http://www.w3newspapers.com/india/|website=w3newspapers.com|accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nIt also owns a music label, [[Zee Music Company]].\n\n==== Properties of ZEEL ====\n\n* [[Zee Network]]\n* [[ZEE5]]\n*[[Zee Turner Limited]] (50% with [[Turner Broadcasting System|Turner]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.esselgroup.com/aboutus.htm|title=Essel Group|date=|publisher=Essel Group|accessdate=2010-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/essel-group-suspends-satellite-platform-for-cable/590803/|title=Essel Group suspends satellite platform for cable|date=2010-03-15|publisher=Financialexpress.com|accessdate=2010-07-16}}</ref>\n*[[Zee ETC Bollywood]]\n\n==== International ====\n\n*[[Zee World]]\n*[[Zee Magic]]\n*[[Zee Mundo]]\n*[[Zee Sine]]\n*[[Zee One]]\n*[[Zee Aflam]]\n*[[Zee Alwan]]\n*[[Zee Bollynova]]\n*[[Zee Russia]]\n*[[Zee TV Canada]]\n*[[Zee Bioskop]]\n*[[Zee Living]]\n*[[Zee Nung]]\n*[[Zee Phim]]\n\n=== Zee Media Corporation Limited (ZMCL) ===\n{{Main|Zee News}}\n\n*[[Zee News]]\n*[[Zee Hindustan]]\n*[[WION (TV channel)|WION]]\n*[[Zee Business]]\n*[[Zee 24 Ghanta]]\n*[[Zee 24 Taas]]\n*[[Zee 24 Kalak]]\n*[[Zee Bihar Jharkhand]]\n*Zee Madhya Pradesh Chhattisgarh\n*Zee Uttar Pradesh Uttarakhand\n*[[Zee Odisha]]\n*[[Zee Punjab Haryana Himachal]]\n*[[Zee Rajasthan]]\n*[[Zee Salaam]]\n\n=== Technology ===\n* [[Dish TV]]\n* [[Siti Cable]]\n\n=== Entertainment ===\n* [[E-City Ventures]]\n* [[Pan India Network Limited]] \u2013 The online gaming company [[Playwin]] is a part of this group.\n* [[Mumbai F.C.|Mumbai FC]]\n\n=== Packaging ===\n* [[Essel Propack]]<ref>[[Hermann Simon]] mentioned this company in his correspondent book as an example of a \"[[Hidden Champions|Hidden Champion]]\". (Simon, Hermann: Hidden Champions of the 21st Century : Success Strategies of unknown World Market Leaders. London: Springer, 2009. {{ISBN|978-0-387-98147-5}}.)</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ecityfilms.com/AboutEsselgroup.aspx?PageID=2 |title=: : : About Essel Group : : : |publisher=Ecityfilms.com |date=2006-02-28 |accessdate=2010-07-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110404030737/http://www.ecityfilms.com/AboutEsselgroup.aspx?PageID=2 |archive-date=4 April 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n=== Infrastructure ===\n* [[Essel Infraprojects]] Limited (EIL) \u2013 This group has started the amusement parks [[Essel World]] and [[Water Kingdom]].\n* [[Suncity Projects]]\n\n=== Precious metal ===\n* [[Shirpur Gold Refinery]] Limited (SGRL) \u2013 precious metal (gold and silver) refinery, fabrication of gold bars, coins and jewellery\n\n=== Education ===\n* Himgiri Zee University (HZU), Dehradun\n* [[Zee Learn]] Limited \u2013 A number of educational projects have been launched by this group. They include:\n** [[KIDZEE]] & [[Mount Litera World]] preschools\n** [[Mount Litera Zee]] & [[Mount Litera World]] Schools\n** [[Zee Institute of Media Arts]] (ZIMA)\n** [[Zee Institute of Creative Art]] (ZICA)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zica.org/|title=Best Animation, VFX and Design Institute India - ZICA|website=zica.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2010/04/09/stories/2010040952960500.htm |title=Essel Group bets big on education |publisher=The Hindu Business Line |date= |accessdate=2010-07-16}}</ref>\n** ZeeQ<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zeeq.in/|title=zeeq.in|website=zeeq.in}}</ref>\n*HZU<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hzu.edu.in/|title=Best Private University in India &#124; Best Private University in Dehradun Uttarakhand - HZU|website=Himgiri Zee University}}</ref>\n*DigiNext Education Pvt Ltd ([https://www.vigyaa.com/ Vigyaa])\n\n=== Charity ===\n* [[Ekal Vidyalaya]]\n* [[Transnational Alternate Learning for Emancipation and Empowerment through Multimedia]] (TALEEM) Research Foundation\n* [[Essel World|EsselWorld-OASIS]]\n\n==Recent developments (2019\u2013present)==\n===Debt and recovery===\nDuring February 2019 reports appeared in the media that Essel Group is in talks to sell<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/media/comcast-atairos-sony-shortlisted-for-stake-sale-talks-by-zee-entertainment/articleshow/68056312.cms|title=Comcast-Atairos, Sony shortlisted for stake sale talks by Zee Entertainment|first1=Gaurav|last1=Laghate|first2=Arijit|last2=Barman|date=19 February 2019|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> their shares from the [[Zee Entertainment Enterprises]] to pay off the debt. \n<br>\n[[Sony|Sony Corporation]], [[Comcast-Atairos]], a firm lead by American cable gaint [[Comcast]] are shortlisted for the bid. However they are competing with technology giant [[Apple Inc.]] and [[Reliance Industries]]\n\nTop Sony officials including Mike Hopkins, chairman of Sony Pictures Television,<ref name=\"auto\"/> and [[Tony Vinciquerra]], chairman of [[Sony Pictures Entertainment]], had visited [[Subhash Chandra]] and his family at his residence shortly after Chandra announced his intent to sell half of the promoter holding in [[Zee Entertainment Enterprises]] to a global strategic investor.\n\nOn April 2 reports saying that<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/zee-entertainment-shares-wobble-after-share-sale-by-promoters/articleshow/68681842.cms|title=Zee Entertainment shares wobble after share sale by promoters|date=2 April 2019|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> some other promoters<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/stocks/zee-entertainment-down-3-after-promoters-sell-stake-3744761.html|title=Zee Entertainment down 3% after promoters sell stake|website=Moneycontrol}}</ref> sell their share worth 332 cr.\n\nOn April 3 media reports [[Sony]] and [[Zee Entertainment Enterprises]] deal off<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/sony-zee-deal-off-for-now-amid-valuation-differences/articleshow/68697156.cms|title=Sony, ZEE deal off for now amid valuation differences|first1=Gaurav|last1=Laghate|first2=Arijit|last2=Barman|date=3 April 2019|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> for now amid valuation differences.which is open the door for [[Comcast-Atairos]]\n\nOn August 1 reports [[Invesco]] Oppenheimer Fund to buy 11% stake in Zee Entertainment<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/news/invesco-oppenheimer-fund-to-buy-11-in-zeel-for-rs-4-224-crore-1564577772129.html|title=Invesco Oppenheimer fund to buy 11% stake in Zee Entertainment for \u20b94,224 cr|first=Tanya|last=Thomas|date=31 July 2019|website=Mint}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Videocon d2h]]\n* [[Tata Sky]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official|http://www.esselgroup.com/}}\n\n{{Essel Group}}\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies of India]]\n[[Category:Conglomerate companies established in 1926]]\n[[Category:Essel Group]]\n[[Category:1926 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-30-500|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Essel Group\n| logo = EsselGroup SVG Logo.svg\n| type = [[Private Company|Private]]\n| foundation = {{start date and age|1926}}\n| founder = [[Jagannath Goenka]]\n| location = [[Mumbai]], [[India]]\n| area_served = [[World]]wide\n| key_people = [[Subhash Chandra]] ([[Chairman]])\n| industry = [[Conglomerate (company)|Conglomerate]]\n| products = [[Mass media|Media]], [[entertainment]], packaging, [[infrastructure]], education, precious metals and technology\n| divisions = [[#Business divisions|See below]]\n| revenue = [[United States dollar|US$]]2.4 billion (2017)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zeelearn.com/about-essel-group/|title=About Essel Group &#124; Zee Learn}}</ref>\n| num_employees